  "local_port": 39910,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some best resume?",
  "response": "A great resume effectively showcases your skills, experience, and accomplishments while being tailored to the job you're applying for. Here are some characteristics of an excellent resume, along with tips to help you create one:\n\n1. **Clear Structure and Layout:**\n   - Use a clean, professional design with clear headings and subheadings.\n   - Choose an easy-to-read font and maintain consistent formatting throughout.\n   - Keep it concise\u2014ideally one page, two pages if you have extensive experience.\n\n2. **Tailored Content:**\n   - Customize your resume for each job application to highlight the most relevant experience and skills.\n   - Use keywords from the job description to pass Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS).\n\n3. **Powerful Summary Statement:**\n   - Start with a strong summary or objective that succinctly highlights your career goals and key skills.\n\n4. **Quantifiable Achievements:**\n   - Focus on achievements rather than just listing duties.\n   - Use numbers, percentages, or other metrics to quantify your accomplishments.\n\n5. **Relevant Experience:**\n   - List work experience in reverse chronological order, with your current or most recent job first.\n   - Include job title, company name, location, and dates of employment.\n\n6. **Skills Section:**\n   - Highlight relevant technical and soft skills, and consider listing them in bullet points for readability.\n\n7. **Education and Certifications:**\n   - Include degrees, certifications, and relevant courses.\n   - Add honors or awards if applicable.\n\n8. **Active Language:**\n   - Use strong action verbs like \"achieved,\" \"developed,\" \"implemented,\" and \"led\" to convey impact.\n\n9. **Contact Information:**\n   - Clearly display your name, phone number, email, and LinkedIn profile or professional website.\n\n10. **Proofread:**\n    - Ensure there are no spelling or grammatical errors. Consider having someone else review it.\n\n11. **Additional Sections (if applicable):**\n    - Include sections like volunteer work, publications, or languages if they are relevant to the role.\n\nBy following these guidelines, you can create a standout resume that effectively communicates your qualifications and helps you secure job interviews.",
